'''Evan Bevan''' (1803–1866) was a Welsh writer of satirical verse.

==Life and work==
Bevan was born into a poor family: his parents were William and Gwenllian Bevan of [[Llangynwyd]], [[Glamorgan]]. As a young adult he moved to [[Ystradfellte]], [[Brecknockshire]] and married there Ann Ifan, a butcher's daughter. He later moved to the [[Pontneddfechan|Pontneathvaughan]] area.<ref name="DWB" />

Bevan gained a mainly local reputation as a writer of satirical verse under the pseudonym Ianto'r Castell,<ref name="DWB" /> some of which is archived at the [[National Library of Wales]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archives.library.wales/index.php/letter-from-evans-john-at-swansea-2|title=D. Rhys Phillips Papers: Letter from Evans, John, at Swansea|work=Identifier letter-from-evans-john-at-swansea-2; C 1297, Archives, National Library of Wales|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://discover.library.wales/44WHELF_NLW_VU1:CSCOP_EVERYTHING:44NLW_ALMA21766777260002419|title=Cofiant ynghyd a gweithiau barddonol y diweddar Evan Bevan, o Bont-nedd-fechan : Cystadleuol yn Eisteddfod Pont-nedd-Fechan . . . Gorph., 3ydd, 1899.|work=Archives, National Library of Wales|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://discover.library.wales/44WHELF_NLW_VU1:CSCOP_EVERYTHING:44NLW_ALMA21860687010002419|title=Cân i helgwn Morgan Phylip Rhys Ysw., Beili Glas, Rhigos / Gan Evan Bevan, Pontneddfechan|work=Archives, National Library of Wales|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://discover.library.wales/44WHELF_NLW_VU1:CSCOP_EVERYTHING:44NLW_ALMA21860690180002419|title=Cân helgwn Morgan Philip Rees, Ysw., o'r Rhigos / Gan Evan Bevan [o] Bontneddfechan|work=Archives, National Library of Wales|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> He died at [[Pontneathvaughan]] in October 1866.<ref name="DWB">{{cite web|title=Evan Bevan|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-BEVA-EVA-1803.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref>

