{{Infobox baseball biography | name= Florence Buccor | image= | image_size= | team= {{small|[[All-American Girls Professional Baseball League]]}} <!-- MISSING DATA - If you or someone you know has information regarding this player, please contact User:MusiCitizen – | position= | birth_date= {{Birth date and age|YY|MM|DD}} | birth_place= | death_date= {{Death date and age|YY|MM|DD|YY|MM|DD}} | death_place= | bats= Right | throws= Right --> | teams= *[[Peoria Redwings]] (1956) |highlights= *Women in Baseball – AAGPBL Permanent Display at Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum (since 1988) }} '''Florence Buccor''' was an [[All-American Girls Professional Baseball League]] player. She was born in [[Jackson, Missouri]].
Buccor is part of the AAGPBL permanent display at the [[Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum]] at [[Cooperstown, New York]] opened in 1988, which is dedicated to the entire league rather than any individual figure.<ref>[http://baseballhall.org/discover/league-of-women-ballplayers Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum Official Website]</ref>
==Notes== Buccor appears as a member of the [[Peoria Redwings]] club during [[Peoria Redwings|its 1956 inaugural season]]. Nevertheless, the league did not have additional information about her, and requires if someone has information regarding this player, please contact them at their website.<ref>[http://www.aagpbl.org/index.cfm/profiles/buccor-katherine/676 All-American Girls Professional Baseball League Official Website]</ref>
