{{refimprove|date=September 2014}}
'''Tetraspores''' are [[red algae]] [[spores]] produced by the [[tetrasporaphyte|tetrasporophytic]] ([[diploid]]) phase in the life history of [[algae]] in the [[red algae|Rhodophyta]] as a result of [[meiosis]].<ref name= "Jones 64">Jones, W.E. Revised and reprinted 1964. A Key to the genera of the British seaweeds.''Field Studies''. Vol 1 (4) pp.1 - 32</ref> The name is derived from the 4 spores that form after this [[meiosis]], the division is of three kinds: cruciate, zonate and tetrahedral.<ref name="Jones 64"/> 

